@startuml iam-group-management
' Requirements: L1-SEC-001, L2-SEC-001
' Source: docs/specs/security/L1.md, docs/specs/security/L2.md
title IAM Group Resource Operations (list, create, update)
autonumber

actor "Administrator" as ADM
participant "HTTP API" as API
participant "Auth Middleware" as MW
participant "IAM Handler" as IAM
database "IAM Store" as DB

note over ADM, DB
  L2-SEC-001: GIVEN an authenticated administrator
  WHEN IAM list/create/update methods are called
  THEN responses follow documented IAM resource structures.
end note

== List groups ==
ADM -> API : GET /api/iam/groups
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : ListGroupsQuery
activate IAM
IAM -> DB : select group records
activate DB
DB --> IAM : group rows
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : ListGroupsResponse (documented group resource structure)
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 200 OK { groups: [ { name, description, members } ] }
deactivate API

== Create group ==
ADM -> API : POST /api/iam/groups { name, description, members }
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : CreateGroupCommand
activate IAM
IAM -> IAM : validate name uniqueness and member references
IAM -> DB : insert group record
activate DB
DB --> IAM : stored
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : GroupResource
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 201 Created { group }
deactivate API

== Update group (membership change) ==
ADM -> API : PATCH /api/iam/groups/{name} { memberAdditions, memberRemovals }
activate API
API -> MW : Authenticate(request)
activate MW
MW --> API : principal (administrator)
deactivate MW
API -> IAM : UpdateGroupCommand
activate IAM
IAM -> DB : load group record
activate DB
DB --> IAM : group row
deactivate DB
IAM -> IAM : resolve member additions/removals against user records
IAM -> DB : persist updated membership
activate DB
DB --> IAM : stored
deactivate DB
IAM --> API : GroupResource (updated)
deactivate IAM
API --> ADM : 200 OK { group }
deactivate API
@enduml
